ientists need to cast aside their commitment to the established order and its ideological support systems, look ahead at the likely outcomes of various interventions and move to the forefront of informed political debate. Providing practical steps and policy programmes, this is ideal for academics and students across a wide range of social science fields and those interested in social inequality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aSocial prediction. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh1 aAtkinson, Rowland, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAtkinson, Rowland, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aBody-Gendrot, Sophie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBurgum, Samuel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCorbett, Steve, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoward, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aEllis, Anthony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJacobs, Keith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMckenzie, Lisa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMckenzie, Lisa, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aOrton, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPahl, Kate, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTaylor, Gretel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWalker, Alan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWard, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWarr, Deborah, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilkinson, Ia